    example: "Roberto de Nobili's approach was revolutionary: he argued that just as the early Church had adapted to Greco-Roman culture, the Indian Church must adapt to Indian culture. He composed hymns and catechetical works in Tamil and Sanskrit. His opponents countered that caste practices were inherently linked to Hindu religion and therefore incompatible with Christian equality. The condemnation of 1744 severely hindered evangelization in India.",
