    example: "Cistercian monasteries transformed the European landscape by draining marshes, clearing forests, and developing advanced farming techniques including selective sheep breeding and sophisticated water management systems. Their austere but beautiful architecture — stripped of Romanesque ornament — anticipated Gothic simplicity. The lay brother system allowed illiterate workers to participate fully in monastic life.",
