    body: "The fall of Constantinople to Sultan Mehmed II on May 29, 1453, was one of the most consequential events in Christian history. The Byzantine capital, which had been the seat of Eastern Christianity for over a thousand years, fell after a siege of fifty-three days. Shortly before the final assault, a union liturgy was celebrated in the Hagia Sophia under the terms of the Council of Florence (1439), with Catholic and Orthodox clergy concelebrating — the last Christian worship in the great church before it became a mosque.",
